WEBVTT

1
00:01:02.930 --> 00:01:06.649
Some people say this world is ugly.

2
00:01:06.650 --> 00:01:09.900
yet it is beautiful at the same time.

3
00:01:10.450 --> 00:01:13.130
l don't know if they are right.

4
00:01:13.810 --> 00:01:17.650
but l'm about to see the world
with fresh eyes.

5
00:04:08.850 --> 00:04:12.449
Wong Kar Mun. l'm giving you
a local anaesthetic now.

6
00:04:12.450 --> 00:04:14.809
The operation will take about 2 hours.

7
00:04:14.810 --> 00:04:17.060
Are you ready?

8
00:04:49.250 --> 00:04:51.529
Who's that?

9
00:04:51.530 --> 00:04:54.729
Quiet!
We don't want to alarm the nurses.

10
00:04:54.730 --> 00:04:56.889
l am in the bed next to yours.

11
00:04:56.890 --> 00:05:00.129
l heard that you
just had an eye operation.

12
00:05:00.130 --> 00:05:02.369
l've had many operations here.

13
00:05:02.370 --> 00:05:05.249
l know the whole hospital.
They're all nice to me.

14
00:05:05.250 --> 00:05:08.169
How old are you?
Why so many operations?

15
00:05:08.170 --> 00:05:12.529
l'm 11. l should have been
in junior high by now.

16
00:05:12.530 --> 00:05:17.009
but my mother says l have a
brain tumour which affects my nerves...

17
00:05:17.010 --> 00:05:22.689
That's why l pass out all the time.
They have to remove it.

18
00:05:22.690 --> 00:05:26.249
But it's so large and dangerous
they have to operate many times.

19
00:05:26.250 --> 00:05:30.249
So l skipped school last year
and stayed here ever since.

20
00:05:30.250 --> 00:05:33.049
You're so young. yet so brave!

21
00:05:33.050 --> 00:05:36.969
Once you can see again.
l'll take you out to play.

22
00:05:36.970 --> 00:05:39.650
The world is really beautiful.

23
00:05:48.490 --> 00:05:53.209
Wong Kar Mun. when l remove
the bandages from your eyes.

24
00:05:53.210 --> 00:05:55.369
it might hurt a little at first.

25
00:05:55.370 --> 00:06:00.980
lf it hurts too much. let me know.
We can always do it tomorrow.

26
00:06:21.890 --> 00:06:24.940
Now let's try.

27
00:06:25.170 --> 00:06:27.980
Open your eyes slowly.

28
00:06:56.930 --> 00:06:59.500
Hey. don't force yourself
if it hurts.

29
00:07:13.010 --> 00:07:14.820
lt hurts!

30
00:07:17.930 --> 00:07:20.169
ls it too painful?

31
00:07:20.170 --> 00:07:23.089
Dr Lo. she must be in a lot of pain!

32
00:07:23.090 --> 00:07:26.689
She hasn't cried out in pain
ever since she was a kid!

33
00:07:26.690 --> 00:07:29.820
Grandma. let Dr Lo do his job.

34
00:07:31.690 --> 00:07:33.489
Please don't be worried about it.

35
00:07:33.490 --> 00:07:35.609
Very few patients experience
full and immediate success.

36
00:07:35.610 --> 00:07:39.530
lt takes time for the eye and brain
to work together.

37
00:07:42.850 --> 00:07:45.260
Come on.

38
00:08:18.690 --> 00:08:20.780
Ying Ying.

39
00:08:28.410 --> 00:08:30.849
Hi. can you see now?

40
00:08:30.850 --> 00:08:33.020
l'm Ying Ying.

41
00:08:38.330 --> 00:08:40.969
Can you really see me?

42
00:08:40.970 --> 00:08:43.650
l think l can see. l'm not sure.

43
00:08:44.210 --> 00:08:46.009
Great! You can see!

44
00:08:46.010 --> 00:08:48.540
Nurse. she can see!

45
00:08:49.210 --> 00:08:52.649
Nurse. her eyes are working!

46
00:08:52.650 --> 00:08:55.660
She sees me! Come quick.

47
00:09:23.250 --> 00:09:25.889
Grandma! The hospital called.

48
00:09:25.890 --> 00:09:28.009
- What?
- Mun can see!

49
00:09:28.010 --> 00:09:30.770
- Let's go to the hospital now.
- OK.

50
00:09:32.450 --> 00:09:35.169
Are you going to discharge me now?

51
00:09:35.170 --> 00:09:36.449
Not so soon.

52
00:09:36.450 --> 00:09:40.809
Every cornea recipient starts off
near-sighted by as much as 1.000 degrees.

53
00:09:40.810 --> 00:09:43.649
Only when your eye muscles
are able to adapt.

54
00:09:43.650 --> 00:09:46.769
will this fall to about 200 degrees.

55
00:09:46.770 --> 00:09:50.409
- When will she have perfect eyesight?
- No one has perfect eyesight.

56
00:09:50.410 --> 00:09:52.649
Most people are near-sighted by
about 100 degrees.

57
00:09:52.650 --> 00:09:56.289
Does that mean she
will need to wear glasses?

58
00:09:56.290 --> 00:10:01.529
That won't be necessary.
All she needs is a pair of sunglasses.

59
00:10:01.530 --> 00:10:03.649
Mun. get some rest.

60
00:10:03.650 --> 00:10:07.340
lf everything goes well.
you can be released early.

61
00:10:12.770 --> 00:10:18.129
You can take off your sunglasses now.
Try to get used to the light gradually.

62
00:10:18.130 --> 00:10:21.289
lf you feel pain.
or if your eyes start watering.

63
00:10:21.290 --> 00:10:25.169
then you should close your eyes
and let your eyes rest.

64
00:10:25.170 --> 00:10:27.889
- Here. l'll help you onto the bed.
- Nurse?

65
00:10:27.890 --> 00:10:30.369
ls there a mirror in every washroom?

66
00:10:30.370 --> 00:10:33.180
Yes. l'll take you there.

67
00:10:46.530 --> 00:10:48.300
Here.

68
00:10:49.530 --> 00:10:51.500
Slowly.

69
00:10:53.250 --> 00:10:56.220
Take your time and call me
if you need anything.

70
00:12:27.090 --> 00:12:29.660
Who's that?

71
00:12:33.210 --> 00:12:36.100
Ying Ying. is that you?

72
00:12:36.250 --> 00:12:38.849
Why are you so quiet?

73
00:12:38.850 --> 00:12:42.689
l'm having another operation tomorrow.

74
00:12:42.690 --> 00:12:46.729
You promised to take me out
once l can see.

75
00:12:46.730 --> 00:12:50.129
We'll go out and have fun
after your operation.

76
00:12:50.130 --> 00:12:52.449
Did they say you can
leave the hospital already?

77
00:12:52.450 --> 00:12:57.180
Not yet. But even if l do.
l can always drop by for a visit.

78
00:12:58.330 --> 00:13:01.249
Let's take a picture together.

79
00:13:01.250 --> 00:13:03.289
- Let's do it outside!
- All right.

80
00:13:03.290 --> 00:13:06.369
- Let's go...
- But where?

81
00:13:06.370 --> 00:13:08.809
Let's go that way!

82
00:13:08.810 --> 00:13:10.729
- What's this?
- A camera!

83
00:13:10.730 --> 00:13:15.049
- A camera?
- Now. look this way.

84
00:13:15.050 --> 00:13:18.260
Ready...1. 2. 3!

85
00:15:24.530 --> 00:15:27.660
Madam. are you all right?

86
00:16:12.010 --> 00:16:14.660
Hello...

87
00:16:26.130 --> 00:16:28.730
l'm freezing...

88
00:17:02.370 --> 00:17:04.769
Send this one to Block C.

89
00:17:04.770 --> 00:17:07.630
We have a full-house in Block B.

90
00:17:31.930 --> 00:17:35.660
Nurse. did the old lady pass away?

91
00:17:37.170 --> 00:17:39.049
Yes. we have taken her away.

92
00:17:39.050 --> 00:17:42.849
But last night.
l saw someone drop by to visit her.

93
00:17:42.850 --> 00:17:46.529
They even went out together.

94
00:17:46.530 --> 00:17:50.980
Are you sure? We don't allow
any visitors here at night.

95
00:17:56.890 --> 00:18:01.860
- Where's Ying Ying?
- She went for an operation this morning.

96
00:18:17.530 --> 00:18:21.449
Dr Lo preferred that
you stay for two more days

97
00:18:21.450 --> 00:18:23.969
but because l'll be away
on flight duty for two weeks.

98
00:18:23.970 --> 00:18:26.689
no one would be able to pick you up.

99
00:18:26.690 --> 00:18:28.809
lt was easier to have you
discharged now.

100
00:18:28.810 --> 00:18:32.380
So you and grandma
can spend more time together.

101
00:18:33.090 --> 00:18:35.449
My... it's already 3:00 pm!

102
00:18:35.450 --> 00:18:38.700
Hope this place
is not too hard to find...

103
00:18:39.290 --> 00:18:41.620
l should have postponed it...

104
00:18:44.890 --> 00:18:49.460
After meeting the therapist.
l'll put you in a taxi.

105
00:18:55.090 --> 00:18:57.260
Hope we won't be too late.

106
00:19:01.690 --> 00:19:04.289
We're only 10 minutes late
for our appointment.

107
00:19:04.290 --> 00:19:07.489
l have to leave for work soon.

108
00:19:07.490 --> 00:19:12.809
l'm sorry. Dr Lo just stepped
out for a few minutes.

109
00:19:12.810 --> 00:19:14.809
- OK.
- There he is.

110
00:19:14.810 --> 00:19:17.889
- ls my three o'clock here?
- Yes. they are.

111
00:19:17.890 --> 00:19:20.140
Mun. let's go.

112
00:19:21.730 --> 00:19:24.529
Let me introduce you
to the nature of my work.

113
00:19:24.530 --> 00:19:29.489
From now on. l am
Ms Wong Kar Mun's psychotherapist.

114
00:19:29.490 --> 00:19:32.249
Since Ms Wong lost her sight
at the age of two.

115
00:19:32.250 --> 00:19:36.649
her visual vocabulary
is extremely limited.

116
00:19:36.650 --> 00:19:40.129
and she has probably forgotten
most of that.

117
00:19:40.130 --> 00:19:41.889
Let's say...

118
00:19:41.890 --> 00:19:43.529
Ms Wong. could you please
remove your glasses.

119
00:19:43.530 --> 00:19:47.370
and let your eyes
get used to the light?

120
00:19:52.450 --> 00:19:55.900
Can you tell me
what's in my hand?

121
00:20:03.370 --> 00:20:06.729
You'll recognize that it's a stapler
once you touch it.

122
00:20:06.730 --> 00:20:11.369
because all your previous knowledge
of objects was through touch. not sight.

123
00:20:11.370 --> 00:20:13.809
Now you are no longer blind.

124
00:20:13.810 --> 00:20:17.769
My job is to help you re-establish
how to use your eyes

125
00:20:17.770 --> 00:20:19.529
and understand what you see.

126
00:20:19.530 --> 00:20:21.809
Actually. l'm not too worried
about that aspect.

127
00:20:21.810 --> 00:20:24.449
What concerns me
is your psychological state.

128
00:20:24.450 --> 00:20:29.369
After regaining sight many patients
end up feeling alienated and fearful.

129
00:20:29.370 --> 00:20:32.529
Dr Lo. is the other Dr Lo
a relative of yours?

130
00:20:32.530 --> 00:20:38.049
You mean Dr C.T. Lo?
Yes. he's my uncle.

131
00:20:38.050 --> 00:20:41.780
So...what time
do you finish work today?

132
00:20:44.170 --> 00:20:46.729
Ms Wong is my last patient
for the day.

133
00:20:46.730 --> 00:20:53.260
You see. l need to catch my flight. Can l
trouble you to send Mun home after this?

134
00:20:54.970 --> 00:20:56.649
l see... of course.

135
00:20:56.650 --> 00:20:58.689
After all. starting from today...

136
00:20:58.690 --> 00:21:01.289
l need to take Ms Wong outdoors
for her training anyway.

137
00:21:01.290 --> 00:21:07.140
You can go ahead.
l'm fine by myself. l'm used to it.

138
00:21:16.530 --> 00:21:19.849
That's you as a little girl.

139
00:21:19.850 --> 00:21:22.729
Your father filmed this
a long time ago

140
00:21:22.730 --> 00:21:26.380
so that you could see it
if your eyes ever healed.

141
00:21:27.090 --> 00:21:30.529
He stopped filming
after he divorced your mother.

142
00:21:30.530 --> 00:21:33.209
That was seven or eight years ago.

143
00:21:33.210 --> 00:21:38.289
Grandma. is it true when Dad comes
back. he'll take us to Vancouver?

144
00:21:38.290 --> 00:21:40.729
l know you don't want to go.

145
00:21:40.730 --> 00:21:44.180
but life in Vancouver
moves at a slower pace.

146
00:21:44.530 --> 00:21:46.449
lt will be better for you.

147
00:21:46.450 --> 00:21:49.889
l can't even read Chinese.
how will l learn English?

148
00:21:49.890 --> 00:21:53.409
Grandma. l don't want to rely
on others forever.

149
00:21:53.410 --> 00:21:56.809
l want to learn to write
and find a job in Hong Kong.

150
00:21:56.810 --> 00:21:58.929
l want to be independent.

151
00:21:58.930 --> 00:22:03.249
Your father would worry about you
going to work.

152
00:22:03.250 --> 00:22:07.540
l have to do the dishes.
l'll leave you to watch this alone.

153
00:22:52.450 --> 00:22:57.609
- Can l help you?
- Have you seen my report card?

154
00:22:57.610 --> 00:23:00.689
No. do you live around here?

155
00:23:00.690 --> 00:23:03.049
Mun. who's that?

156
00:23:03.050 --> 00:23:05.489
lt's a little boy. Grandma.

157
00:23:05.490 --> 00:23:09.980
Did a report card ever turn up
on our balcony?

158
00:23:10.930 --> 00:23:13.980
That kid is teasing you.
Just ignore him.

159
00:24:35.210 --> 00:24:39.289
Kid. what are you eating?

160
00:24:39.290 --> 00:24:42.100
l'm hungry.

161
00:24:46.050 --> 00:24:49.020
What's your problem?

162
00:25:44.370 --> 00:25:47.809
Everyone. we have
two pieces of good news today.

163
00:25:47.810 --> 00:25:49.660
First...

164
00:25:50.690 --> 00:25:56.110
Ms Tone Deaf
had a successful operation!

165
00:25:59.450 --> 00:26:02.969
And second.
for our Christmas charity concert

166
00:26:02.970 --> 00:26:07.100
we will be performing with
Vanessa Mae!

167
00:26:34.690 --> 00:26:38.900
Mr Cheng. why haven't l
received the practice schedule?

168
00:26:44.490 --> 00:26:48.369
Mun. you know. after all
we're an organization for the blind.

169
00:26:48.370 --> 00:26:50.689
You're always welcome
to come to practice

170
00:26:50.690 --> 00:26:54.089
but perhaps you should
do something else for the performance.

171
00:26:54.090 --> 00:26:56.569
such as coordination.
or taking care of our members.

172
00:26:56.570 --> 00:27:00.729
l can even arrange for you
to help out at the centre.

173
00:27:00.730 --> 00:27:05.009
Mr Cheng. l really want to
take part in this performance.

174
00:27:05.010 --> 00:27:08.729
l've practiced so long for this concert!

175
00:27:08.730 --> 00:27:12.300
l understand. but...

176
00:27:13.770 --> 00:27:15.529
Excuse me. Mr Cheng.

177
00:27:15.530 --> 00:27:19.609
Vanessa Mae's agent wants us
to fax over her schedule.

178
00:27:19.610 --> 00:27:22.009
l'll be with you right away.

179
00:27:22.010 --> 00:27:24.929
Mun. Mun?

180
00:27:24.930 --> 00:27:30.220
Let's discuss this again.
l have to go.

181
00:28:54.090 --> 00:28:55.889
- Grandma!
- Are you leaving?

182
00:28:55.890 --> 00:28:58.689
- Yes. to class.
- Come back early for dinner.

183
00:28:58.690 --> 00:29:02.610
- l've prepared some special turnip soup.
- Bye!

184
00:29:03.610 --> 00:29:07.729
Have you seen my report card?

185
00:29:07.730 --> 00:29:11.180
Didn't you find it yet?

186
00:29:11.690 --> 00:29:14.340
l really haven't seen it.

187
00:29:17.530 --> 00:29:20.820
Perhaps you should ask someone else.

188
00:29:39.450 --> 00:29:41.860
Ying Ying!

189
00:29:43.010 --> 00:29:45.569
Excuse me. l'd like to talk to her.

190
00:29:45.570 --> 00:29:48.860
Look what l've brought for you?

191
00:29:49.570 --> 00:29:52.969
l've just had chemo-therapy.

192
00:29:52.970 --> 00:29:55.980
l'll throw up if l eat.

193
00:29:58.170 --> 00:30:02.700
Then we'll save it
for when you get better.

194
00:30:31.330 --> 00:30:34.649
lf only we had believed him
just that once.

195
00:30:34.650 --> 00:30:37.769
or given him a chance to explain.

196
00:30:37.770 --> 00:30:40.530
he might still be here
playing video games.

197
00:30:41.290 --> 00:30:45.500
Who would have expected him
to jump off just like that?

198
00:30:46.450 --> 00:30:50.180
Suicide is a dreadful sin.

199
00:30:51.770 --> 00:30:53.809
The souls of those who commit suicide

200
00:30:53.810 --> 00:30:57.260
are obliged to repeat
their painful deaths everyday.

201
00:30:57.650 --> 00:31:01.289
To help him break out of this
vicious cycle of pain.

202
00:31:01.290 --> 00:31:05.169
we need to tackle
the cause of his suicide.

203
00:31:05.170 --> 00:31:08.860
Only then can his soul
leave this world in peace.

204
00:31:10.810 --> 00:31:14.209
Have you ever considered
he might be telling the truth?

205
00:31:14.210 --> 00:31:18.260
Perhaps he really did lose
his report card.

206
00:33:19.610 --> 00:33:22.329
Have you been teaching
calligraphy long?

207
00:33:22.330 --> 00:33:23.969
Yes. many years indeed.

208
00:33:23.970 --> 00:33:29.689
l'll teach you how to hold the brush.

209
00:33:29.690 --> 00:33:33.809
Use your thumb and middle finger
and form a circle like this.

210
00:33:33.810 --> 00:33:38.340
Like this. try.

211
00:33:39.570 --> 00:33:43.649
Very few want to
learn calligraphy nowadays.

212
00:33:43.650 --> 00:33:48.769
l used to teach 3 lessons a week.

213
00:33:48.770 --> 00:33:53.300
Now it is down to only one.

214
00:33:53.850 --> 00:33:58.529
l'll let you try writing by yourself.

215
00:33:58.530 --> 00:34:01.060
Try it yourself.

216
00:34:24.570 --> 00:34:27.500
Why are you sitting in my chair?

217
00:34:57.530 --> 00:35:00.290
Why are you sitting in my chair?

218
00:35:08.570 --> 00:35:12.380
What is this? What is going on?

219
00:35:14.450 --> 00:35:18.140
What are you looking for?
Are you OK?

220
00:35:22.090 --> 00:35:27.660
What happened?
Are you feeling unwell?

221
00:35:30.930 --> 00:35:34.849
- ls Dr Lo here?
- Ms Wong. you are early.

222
00:35:34.850 --> 00:35:37.929
Your next appointment
isn't until Friday.

223
00:35:37.930 --> 00:35:41.460
He won't be back from
his meeting until 5:00 pm.

224
00:35:42.530 --> 00:35:44.569
Will he definitely be here at 5:00 pm?

225
00:35:44.570 --> 00:35:48.980
lf it's urgent. l can page him for you now.

226
00:35:49.890 --> 00:35:52.490
l'll be back at 5:00 pm.

227
00:37:51.570 --> 00:37:54.170
You can see them too?

228
00:37:54.890 --> 00:37:57.929
They don't usually want to be seen.

229
00:37:57.930 --> 00:38:00.580
But you'll get used to it.

230
00:38:01.370 --> 00:38:04.409
All the stores nearby
have been bought up.

231
00:38:04.410 --> 00:38:06.729
only my boss refuses to sell.

232
00:38:06.730 --> 00:38:09.460
He seems to be expecting
his wife and child to visit.

233
00:38:10.290 --> 00:38:13.050
Actually. he can't see them at all.

234
00:38:58.050 --> 00:39:01.260
There was a car accident over there...

235
00:39:45.730 --> 00:39:47.580
Mun!

236
00:39:48.770 --> 00:39:54.190
My secretary said you were asking
for me. What's the matter?

237
00:40:07.090 --> 00:40:12.129
- Will you help me?
- Of course. l will.

238
00:40:12.130 --> 00:40:14.730
Your eyes hurt?

239
00:40:16.290 --> 00:40:20.609
- Will you believe me?
- Yes.

240
00:40:20.610 --> 00:40:22.889
What is it?

241
00:40:22.890 --> 00:40:27.580
The shadows...
they come to bring the dead.

242
00:40:28.330 --> 00:40:30.980
What shadow?

243
00:40:33.290 --> 00:40:36.849
When l was at the hospital...

244
00:40:36.850 --> 00:40:39.820
l saw a man.

245
00:40:40.970 --> 00:40:44.889
He...he took that old lady with him.

246
00:40:44.890 --> 00:40:49.689
The next morning.
the old lady was dead.

247
00:40:49.690 --> 00:40:54.969
My room keeps changing suddenly
into a different room.

248
00:40:54.970 --> 00:40:59.340
l even saw a person
missing her lower body.

249
00:41:07.530 --> 00:41:12.209
When he rushed over.
it was like an electric shock.

250
00:41:12.210 --> 00:41:15.460
My whole body went numb.

251
00:41:23.810 --> 00:41:27.380
Calm down and tell me slowly.

252
00:41:36.010 --> 00:41:38.660
When l was little...

253
00:41:39.330 --> 00:41:41.980
Grandma told me...

254
00:41:42.410 --> 00:41:45.580
l was not an ordinary child.

255
00:41:46.130 --> 00:41:49.169
God had given me some obstacles

256
00:41:49.170 --> 00:41:54.300
so that l would grow up to be
an extraordinary person.

257
00:41:56.370 --> 00:42:01.609
Now l understand what it means
to be extraordinary.

258
00:42:01.610 --> 00:42:06.809
An extraordinary person
can see things others can't

259
00:42:06.810 --> 00:42:10.460
and feel pain that others won't feel.

260
00:42:13.930 --> 00:42:19.020
Maybe. l was never meant
to see this world.

261
00:42:20.530 --> 00:42:26.849
l don't want to go
to bed terrified every night

262
00:42:26.850 --> 00:42:29.940
then awaken
to horrors every morning.

263
00:42:32.130 --> 00:42:35.660
l just want to be an ordinary person.

264
00:42:36.450 --> 00:42:39.780
Dr Lo. can you help me?

265
00:42:42.250 --> 00:42:45.110
Yes. of course l will.

266
00:42:49.570 --> 00:42:52.769
One of my psychology professors
from the States

267
00:42:52.770 --> 00:42:56.329
has just come to Hong Kong to visit.
Let's go see him tomorrow.

268
00:42:56.330 --> 00:42:59.380
He might be able to help.

269
00:43:14.650 --> 00:43:19.100
How can you help me
when you don't believe me?

270
00:43:51.930 --> 00:43:54.009
What's going on?

271
00:43:54.010 --> 00:43:57.729
Excuse me. l have to go.
Call me if you need anything.

272
00:43:57.730 --> 00:43:59.580
Goodbye.

273
00:44:00.530 --> 00:44:03.129
- Who's that?
- A friend.

274
00:44:03.130 --> 00:44:06.289
He asked your sister to
take something to the States.

275
00:44:06.290 --> 00:44:08.009
Yes. that's right.

276
00:44:08.010 --> 00:44:11.689
You are home early. Aren't you
supposed to be back next week?

277
00:44:11.690 --> 00:44:15.649
Well... a co-worker
switched her shift with mine.

278
00:44:15.650 --> 00:44:19.060
Why don't you go up?
lt's smoky here.

279
00:48:16.090 --> 00:48:18.489
Have you seen my report card?

280
00:48:18.490 --> 00:48:21.249
Stop asking me!
l've already told you l haven't seen it!

281
00:48:21.250 --> 00:48:24.780
Have you seen my report card?

282
00:48:36.770 --> 00:48:38.420
15th Floor. Unit C

283
00:50:48.090 --> 00:50:50.969
Uncle. listen to me.

284
00:50:50.970 --> 00:50:51.969
No way!

285
00:50:51.970 --> 00:50:54.129
Only you can help us with this!

286
00:50:54.130 --> 00:50:56.809
l've already said no!

287
00:50:56.810 --> 00:51:00.409
lf you still respect me as your uncle.
and respect yourself as my nephew.

288
00:51:00.410 --> 00:51:04.380
you should have never
approached me with this!

289
00:51:04.650 --> 00:51:07.329
You should know only too well

290
00:51:07.330 --> 00:51:09.809
what the medical ethics are
regarding organ transplants.

291
00:51:09.810 --> 00:51:12.529
And you should also know

292
00:51:12.530 --> 00:51:15.169
that the identity of the cornea donor
is concealed from me.

293
00:51:15.170 --> 00:51:17.209
What shadow?

294
00:51:17.210 --> 00:51:23.100
One cornea transplant and she starts
seeing ghosts? You actually believe that?

295
00:51:23.770 --> 00:51:27.580
- What if l do?
- Then we have even less to talk about!

296
00:51:28.490 --> 00:51:30.769
Uncle...

297
00:51:30.770 --> 00:51:34.420
Don't tell me
you fell for your own patient.

298
00:51:43.930 --> 00:51:47.369
- Hello?
- Dr Lo. is that you?

299
00:51:47.370 --> 00:51:51.900
Mun is in trouble!
Can you come over immediately?

300
00:51:52.570 --> 00:51:54.860
Yes. right away.

301
00:51:59.330 --> 00:52:03.940
Yes. l admit.
She's more than a patient to me.

302
00:52:14.210 --> 00:52:16.890
Mun!

303
00:52:26.010 --> 00:52:28.609
How long do you plan on hiding
in this little room?

304
00:52:28.610 --> 00:52:31.529
Five years? Seven? Or ten?

305
00:52:31.530 --> 00:52:34.660
You have to confront your problem
sooner or later.

306
00:52:36.130 --> 00:52:39.900
You want to play violin?
Go play with the troupe!

307
00:52:41.530 --> 00:52:44.049
l can accept you
pretending to be blind.

308
00:52:44.050 --> 00:52:47.500
But even then you didn't
isolate yourself here.

309
00:52:53.650 --> 00:52:56.460
l just want to help.

310
00:55:05.330 --> 00:55:07.420
Mun!

311
00:55:27.850 --> 00:55:29.500
Mun.

312
00:55:39.730 --> 00:55:43.569
Ying Ying. what are you doing here?

313
00:55:43.570 --> 00:55:46.980
l can leave the hospital now.

314
00:55:48.730 --> 00:55:50.929
You can?

315
00:55:50.930 --> 00:55:55.180
Yes. l don't need any more operations.
l can go to school now.

316
00:55:58.970 --> 00:56:01.900
Then once l'm out of here...

317
00:56:03.330 --> 00:56:07.449
we can go out...

318
00:56:07.450 --> 00:56:11.660
we can take pictures. we can even...

319
00:56:16.450 --> 00:56:19.180
l'm so happy that you can see now...

320
00:56:25.210 --> 00:56:27.970
because this world is really beautiful.

321
00:56:34.930 --> 00:56:37.329
Ying Ying...

322
00:56:37.330 --> 00:56:40.369
lt's all right. Cheer up.

323
00:56:40.370 --> 00:56:44.210
Be strong and things
will work out for the best.

324
00:56:49.010 --> 00:56:52.020
l have to go now.

325
00:57:29.850 --> 00:57:32.660
Ying Ying!

326
00:58:09.650 --> 00:58:13.460
Wong Kar Mun. l want to tell you...

327
00:58:14.130 --> 00:58:17.060
Ying Ying has already...

328
00:58:21.170 --> 00:58:25.250
l know... l just saw her.

329
00:58:26.610 --> 00:58:30.060
l know she's dead.

330
00:59:20.810 --> 00:59:23.329
What are you looking at?

331
00:59:23.330 --> 00:59:25.420
Ying Ying.

332
00:59:28.730 --> 00:59:30.740
Can you see her?

333
00:59:38.930 --> 00:59:41.690
lt wasn't her.

334
00:59:42.130 --> 00:59:45.700
Don't know why
she didn't show up today.

335
00:59:50.210 --> 00:59:53.070
Are you not afraid anymore?

336
00:59:55.930 --> 01:00:01.090
l don't think l have a choice.
l see all of these things anyway.

337
01:00:01.690 --> 01:00:05.460
At least. l get to see
the people l care about.

338
01:00:17.410 --> 01:00:22.500
- What's this?
- Ying Ying made this for you.

339
01:00:31.450 --> 01:00:35.420
- What's written on it?
- ''Don't forget me''

340
01:00:41.330 --> 01:00:46.129
She put in the wrong photo though.
Who's this?

341
01:00:46.130 --> 01:00:50.700
lt's you.
Don't you recognize yourself yet?

342
01:01:11.330 --> 01:01:14.289
What is going on?

343
01:01:14.290 --> 01:01:16.890
Who are you?

344
01:01:24.690 --> 01:01:27.980
Who the hell are you?

345
01:02:02.450 --> 01:02:07.849
We believe that the last consciousness
of a mortal carries onto the afterlife.

346
01:02:07.850 --> 01:02:12.249
That is. the very thought
of a person in his final moment...

347
01:02:12.250 --> 01:02:14.049
would become the eternal
consciousness of his soul.

348
01:02:14.050 --> 01:02:16.249
Those who die a sudden death

349
01:02:16.250 --> 01:02:19.649
have no recollection
of the instance of death.

350
01:02:19.650 --> 01:02:23.449
Their souls remain in this world
as if they're still alive.

351
01:02:23.450 --> 01:02:26.249
But there are others
who intentionally refuse to leave.

352
01:02:26.250 --> 01:02:29.289
mostly due to unresolved problems
during their lifetime.

353
01:02:29.290 --> 01:02:32.729
These souls can't be consoled
while their problems remain.

354
01:02:32.730 --> 01:02:36.329
There is only one way to help them.

355
01:02:36.330 --> 01:02:39.729
and that is to resolve
what they left unsettled.

356
01:02:39.730 --> 01:02:43.089
The woman Ms Wong keeps seeing
after resuming her sight.

357
01:02:43.090 --> 01:02:46.930
We have to resolve her problems
so that she can move on.

358
01:03:05.890 --> 01:03:08.489
l hope l haven't done anything wrong.

359
01:03:08.490 --> 01:03:11.449
Even if it's wrong. it'd be my fault.

360
01:03:11.450 --> 01:03:13.820
And l won't regret it.

361
01:03:15.370 --> 01:03:17.729
Were you reincarnated
into the wrong body?

362
01:03:17.730 --> 01:03:21.260
Why are you so different
from the rest of the family?

363
01:03:25.570 --> 01:03:28.220
Be careful.

364
01:03:35.770 --> 01:03:40.180
Bangkok. Thailand

365
01:03:47.570 --> 01:03:50.089
Did Dr Lo believe you in the end?

366
01:03:50.090 --> 01:03:53.329
Let's just say Dr Lo is not involved.

367
01:03:53.330 --> 01:03:55.849
He's a professional after all -

368
01:03:55.850 --> 01:03:57.889
you know what l mean?

369
01:03:57.890 --> 01:04:01.009
Yes. Are we close?

370
01:04:01.010 --> 01:04:03.009
l'm not sure.

371
01:04:03.010 --> 01:04:06.369
lt says here that her Chinese name
was Chiu Wai Ling.

372
01:04:06.370 --> 01:04:10.580
A Thai born Chinese.
Here are her hospital records.

373
01:04:46.050 --> 01:04:50.089
This is Siam-Rach Hospital.

374
01:04:50.090 --> 01:04:55.409
Sl-AM-LA?
This is probably the place.

375
01:04:55.410 --> 01:04:58.620
Let's get off to take a look.

376
01:05:38.690 --> 01:05:42.220
Please come help.

377
01:05:43.610 --> 01:05:45.380
Can l help you?

378
01:06:20.010 --> 01:06:21.860
He's not here now.

379
01:07:27.890 --> 01:07:30.220
Wah!

380
01:07:31.890 --> 01:07:33.980
Wah!

381
01:07:34.490 --> 01:07:35.889
What is it?

382
01:07:35.890 --> 01:07:38.329
- This is the place.
- What place?

383
01:07:38.330 --> 01:07:40.849
The place l've been
having nightmares about.

384
01:07:40.850 --> 01:07:42.649
Nightmares?

385
01:07:42.650 --> 01:07:45.410
This has to be it!

386
01:07:46.970 --> 01:07:48.729
Doctor Eak.

387
01:07:48.730 --> 01:07:53.700
- What's the matter?
- You have two visitors.

388
01:07:53.850 --> 01:07:57.420
Mister. this is Dr Eak.

389
01:08:20.490 --> 01:08:24.489
- Are you two from Hong Kong?
- You speak Mandarin?

390
01:08:24.490 --> 01:08:27.170
Can you help us?

391
01:08:28.730 --> 01:08:32.729
Sorry. l can't disclose
our hospital record.

392
01:08:32.730 --> 01:08:36.489
This is our hospital policy.
Please understand.

393
01:08:36.490 --> 01:08:40.369
Wait! We need to see
the donor's family urgently.

394
01:08:40.370 --> 01:08:44.209
Could you perhaps ask them
if they're willing to meet us?

395
01:08:44.210 --> 01:08:47.129
Her family will not be willing
to meet with you.

396
01:08:47.130 --> 01:08:49.849
Who are you to Ling?

397
01:08:49.850 --> 01:08:53.340
- Please leave.
- Wait!

398
01:08:54.170 --> 01:08:59.620
After l got Ling's corneas.
l started to see things that she saw.

399
01:09:07.650 --> 01:09:13.409
Ling was a sad and lonely girl.
All of the villagers stayed away from her.

400
01:09:13.410 --> 01:09:15.329
Why?

401
01:09:15.330 --> 01:09:19.009
From time to time.
she would weep outside someone's door.

402
01:09:19.010 --> 01:09:23.689
Afterwards. a person in that house
would pass away.

403
01:09:23.690 --> 01:09:26.689
So everyone took her to be a witch

404
01:09:26.690 --> 01:09:30.249
and always chased her away
when they saw her.

405
01:09:30.250 --> 01:09:33.849
The children treated her
like a monster.

406
01:09:33.850 --> 01:09:38.449
even l threw stones at her
when l was a kid.

407
01:09:38.450 --> 01:09:42.609
Because none of you could believe
that she foresaw death?

408
01:09:42.610 --> 01:09:45.769
Maybe it was because of fear.

409
01:09:45.770 --> 01:09:48.530
So. do you believe it now?

410
01:10:00.370 --> 01:10:02.380
This is it.

411
01:10:18.850 --> 01:10:23.420
Mrs Chui. these two friends
are from Hong Kong.

412
01:10:24.810 --> 01:10:27.489
Nobody welcomed Ling.

413
01:10:27.490 --> 01:10:31.570
So she hardly ever
set foot in the village.

414
01:10:32.930 --> 01:10:34.969
Yet. on the night of the fire.

415
01:10:34.970 --> 01:10:39.049
many people saw her running around
and shouting hysterically

416
01:10:39.050 --> 01:10:41.650
as if talking to herself.

417
01:10:42.090 --> 01:10:44.569
Since everyone detested Ling.

418
01:10:44.570 --> 01:10:47.489
no one paid any attention to her.

419
01:10:47.490 --> 01:10:53.140
Some villagers even threw water
on her to drive her away.

420
01:10:54.050 --> 01:10:57.569
Around midnight. a big fire erupted

421
01:10:57.570 --> 01:11:00.049
and kept burning till noon
the next day.

422
01:11:00.050 --> 01:11:04.089
Among the deceased.
300 were burnt beyond recognition.

423
01:11:04.090 --> 01:11:08.380
- How exactly did Ling die?
- She hanged herself.

424
01:11:14.850 --> 01:11:18.580
Ling killed herself
the day after the big fire.

425
01:11:25.170 --> 01:11:27.500
ls Mrs Chui all right?

426
01:11:28.130 --> 01:11:30.020
She's fine.

427
01:11:32.330 --> 01:11:34.769
So you too believed that
she wasn't insane.

428
01:11:34.770 --> 01:11:37.849
but that she only saw things
no one else could.

429
01:11:37.850 --> 01:11:41.009
She foresaw a big disaster
and tried to warn everyone.

430
01:11:41.010 --> 01:11:43.089
but no one listened to her.

431
01:11:43.090 --> 01:11:45.569
l don't understand
any of this spiritual stuff.

432
01:11:45.570 --> 01:11:51.100
l just want you two to know
that Ling was a kind person...

433
01:11:51.850 --> 01:11:54.940
and she had a tough life.

434
01:11:55.690 --> 01:11:58.500
Can l take a look at Ling's room?

435
01:12:18.250 --> 01:12:21.129
Tonight...l want to stay here.

436
01:12:21.130 --> 01:12:24.689
l'll take you to Ling's grave
tomorrow morning.

437
01:12:24.690 --> 01:12:28.929
Thank you for being so considerate.

438
01:12:28.930 --> 01:12:31.580
You should go to bed now.

439
01:12:33.450 --> 01:12:37.780
All right. l'll stay next door.
Shout if anything happens.

440
01:13:43.690 --> 01:13:46.449
l know you've wanted me
to come here all this time.

441
01:13:46.450 --> 01:13:48.609
Well. here l am now.

442
01:13:48.610 --> 01:13:51.540
What do you want to tell me?

443
01:14:16.890 --> 01:14:20.970
...ill-fated...ill-fated...

444
01:14:22.450 --> 01:14:25.180
Hurry...take her to the hospital.

445
01:14:31.170 --> 01:14:34.409
You should be ashamed of yourself.

446
01:14:34.410 --> 01:14:37.900
You're a curse!
You speak evil.

447
01:14:45.210 --> 01:14:47.929
l told you not to come here!

448
01:14:47.930 --> 01:14:52.180
She's evil! Don't even talk to her!
Never play with her again!

449
01:15:01.370 --> 01:15:03.969
Go save him! Save my boy.

450
01:15:03.970 --> 01:15:06.409
Help him... Make him breathe.

451
01:15:06.410 --> 01:15:10.100
What have you done to my boy?
You little witch!

452
01:16:19.450 --> 01:16:24.049
Mrs Chui. l know how to help Ling.
Let's go upstairs to see her.

453
01:16:24.050 --> 01:16:27.849
Her most painful time
was not in the past. but it's now.

454
01:16:27.850 --> 01:16:29.329
Since she killed herself.

455
01:16:29.330 --> 01:16:31.969
she's been trapped in a time warp
constantly repeating her suicide.

456
01:16:31.970 --> 01:16:36.129
How can someone
who's dead die again?

457
01:16:36.130 --> 01:16:40.540
Listen to me.
very soon she'll appear upstairs.

458
01:16:43.090 --> 01:16:47.369
- Let's go up to see her!
- l won't see her!

459
01:16:47.370 --> 01:16:49.929
l spent my whole life protecting her.

460
01:16:49.930 --> 01:16:52.489
l never once gave up on her.

461
01:16:52.490 --> 01:16:55.809
but she gave up on herself!

462
01:16:55.810 --> 01:16:59.780
For that l can never forgive her!

463
01:17:04.850 --> 01:17:06.489
Just listen.

464
01:17:06.490 --> 01:17:09.060
l'm sure you hear this sound
every night.

465
01:17:09.890 --> 01:17:12.620
Ling died at three o'clock. didn't she?

466
01:17:22.010 --> 01:17:25.609
Mrs Chui. come with me
and you'll understand!

467
01:17:25.610 --> 01:17:28.470
l'm not going upstairs!

468
01:18:16.570 --> 01:18:17.370
Mom...

469
01:18:24.930 --> 01:18:27.740
Help me...

470
01:18:32.410 --> 01:18:34.140
Ling?

471
01:18:34.850 --> 01:18:38.140
Help me...

472
01:18:47.810 --> 01:18:49.900
Help me!

473
01:19:17.410 --> 01:19:19.929
Help me...help me...

474
01:19:19.930 --> 01:19:21.889
ls it Ling?

475
01:19:21.890 --> 01:19:24.540
ls it really Ling?

476
01:19:26.730 --> 01:19:30.289
Mom...

477
01:19:30.290 --> 01:19:32.969
Help me...

478
01:19:32.970 --> 01:19:36.890
Ling. you were the one who left me...

479
01:19:38.610 --> 01:19:43.689
you were the one who left me...

480
01:19:43.690 --> 01:19:49.420
Mom... Help me...

481
01:19:58.130 --> 01:20:01.180
Ling. Mummy is coming!

482
01:20:02.410 --> 01:20:04.340
Ling! Ling!

483
01:20:08.690 --> 01:20:12.489
My girl. mummy's right here.

484
01:20:12.490 --> 01:20:14.980
Don't be afraid.

485
01:20:16.330 --> 01:20:19.209
No one can bully you anymore.

486
01:20:19.210 --> 01:20:24.060
Mom. l'm so sorry.

487
01:20:24.970 --> 01:20:27.830
l was wrong.

488
01:20:28.410 --> 01:20:31.140
Please forgive me.

489
01:20:34.450 --> 01:20:37.540
l have already forgiven you.

490
01:20:51.330 --> 01:20:55.020
Mun. what happened?

491
01:20:56.210 --> 01:20:58.540
Are you all right?

492
01:24:18.890 --> 01:24:22.009
Go that way! Move over.

493
01:24:22.010 --> 01:24:24.329
Hurry! Pull him out.

494
01:24:24.330 --> 01:24:27.460
Careful! Come on. keep pulling.

495
01:24:34.450 --> 01:24:38.450
Over there! Move!

496
01:26:08.290 --> 01:26:10.060
Get out!

497
01:26:13.290 --> 01:26:16.649
Something's happening! Run!
Granny. leave your house now!

498
01:26:16.650 --> 01:26:19.300
Leave your house now!

499
01:26:21.370 --> 01:26:23.529
Run for your life!

500
01:26:23.530 --> 01:26:25.409
Get out! Quick! Run!

501
01:26:25.410 --> 01:26:27.860
Get out! Run.

502
01:26:28.570 --> 01:26:30.780
Run for your life!

503
01:26:37.770 --> 01:26:41.180
Run! A disaster is coming!

504
01:27:02.050 --> 01:27:03.929
Run! Run now!

505
01:27:03.930 --> 01:27:05.980
What's she saying?

506
01:27:33.050 --> 01:27:34.009
Mun!

507
01:27:34.010 --> 01:27:36.660
Go. go. go... Move over.

508
01:27:48.490 --> 01:27:50.580
Move over!

509
01:28:12.890 --> 01:28:14.410
Listen to me.

510
01:30:23.050 --> 01:30:25.100
Mun...

511
01:31:26.330 --> 01:31:30.769
Ever since that day.
Ling never appears again.

512
01:31:30.770 --> 01:31:32.729
l hold no resentment towards her.

513
01:31:32.730 --> 01:31:37.049
Since l saw and experienced
the same pain that she did.

514
01:31:37.050 --> 01:31:43.060
But aside from pain. l saw beauty.

515
01:31:43.850 --> 01:31:47.409
l no longer ask. ''Why l am blind?''

516
01:31:47.410 --> 01:31:52.289
For l've seen some of the most
beautiful things in this world.

517
01:31:52.290 --> 01:31:55.420
Things l'll never forget.
